# Database & Drizzle — Mandatory Rules

## NEVER do any of the following

- **NEVER run raw SQL** (psql, pg, etc.) to modify the database schema or data
- **NEVER use `DROP TABLE`**, `ALTER TABLE`, `CREATE TABLE`, or any DDL directly
- **NEVER bypass drizzle** for any database operation
- **NEVER use `db:push`** — it does not create migration files and breaks deploys

## How we manage the database

1. **Schema changes** go in `web/db/schema/*.ts` (drizzle schema files)
2. **Migrations** are generated via `npx drizzle-kit generate` (interactive — user runs it)
3. **Migrations are applied** via `node scripts/migrate.js` (runs on Vercel deploy)
4. **Local DB sync** uses `npx drizzle-kit migrate` or `node scripts/migrate.js`

## Workflow for schema changes

1. Edit the schema file (e.g. `web/db/schema/content.ts`)
2. Ask the user to run `npx drizzle-kit generate --name <migration_name>` in their terminal
3. Review the generated `.sql` file in `web/db/migrations/`
4. Ask the user to run `npx drizzle-kit migrate` to apply locally
5. Update `docs/data-model-specification.md` if needed

## Why this matters

- `scripts/migrate.js` runs on every Vercel deploy (`vercel-build` script)
- Production and preview deploys depend on migration files existing
- Raw SQL changes are invisible to the migration system and WILL break deploys
- `drizzle-kit generate` is interactive (rename disambiguation) — the user must run it
